<h2>Chapter 7: Where AI Falls Short for Home Service</h2>
<p>Four areas where AI is not yet ready to replace human judgment.</p>
<h3>Complex Diagnoses</h3>
<p>Strange noises, intermittent problems, unique installations. Technicians must diagnose in person. AI cannot replace technical expertise.</p>
<h3>Customer Crisis Management</h3>
<p>Flooded basement at 3am with elderly customer. AI handles initial intake but emergency response requires human dispatch decision and empathetic communication.</p>
<h3>Unique Job Pricing</h3>
<p>Custom projects, large commercial work, unusual installations. AI estimates well for standard work but struggles with non-standard scenarios.</p>
<h3>Trust-Building During Initial Visits</h3>
<p>The first time a customer uses your service, the technician's behavior determines whether they become a repeat customer. AI cannot replace the in-person interaction.</p>
<p>The pattern: AI handles routine and administrative scale. Humans handle complex diagnosis and emotional moments. Both are needed.</p>
